OL,3,CJersey's Council of Ministers meeting
OL,4,Cto discuss ferry dilemma
OL,6,FSpeaking to ITV Channel, Deputy
OL,7,FKirsten Morel, said: "We're not at the
OL,8,Fposition of going with two operators.
OL,9,FWe're at the position where Jersey
OL,10,Fwants and needs more information from
OL,11,Fboth operators to ensure things such
OL,12,Fas financial stability.
OL,14,F"We need to make sure we chose a
OL,15,Fprovider who can provide services for
OL,16,Fthe full 15 years. We don't want
OL,17,FJersey or Guernsey tax payers to be in
OL,18,Fa position where they are forced into
OL,19,Fsome rescue packages."
